--- CompleteMazeBuilder Random Player Spawn - 2026-03-04
+++ Assets/Scripts/Core/06_Maze/CompleteMazeBuilder.cs

FEATURE ADDED:
==============
Random player spawn position inside maze (not always at entrance)

INSPECTOR OPTIONS:
==================
Added new settings in CompleteMazeBuilder component:

[Header("🎲 Random Spawn")]
- randomPlayerSpawn (default: true) - Enable/disable random spawn
- minSpawnDistanceFromWall (default: 1.5m) - Safety margin from walls

CHANGES:
========

PlacePlayerAtSpawn():
  - Now checks randomPlayerSpawn flag
  - If true: calls GetRandomSpawnPosition()
  - If false: uses entrance room or default position
  - Player created if not found (same as before)

GetRandomSpawnPosition() - NEW METHOD:
  - Gets maze grid from MazeGenerator
  - Tries up to 20 random positions
  - Picks random cell (avoiding edges)
  - Checks if cell is empty (Wall.None)
  - Returns valid spawn position at eye height (1m)
  - Falls back to entrance or default if no valid position found

SPAWN LOGIC:
============
if (randomPlayerSpawn == true)
  → Find random empty cell in maze
  → Spawn player at cell center (eye height: 1m)
else if (entranceRoomPosition exists)
  → Spawn at entrance room
else
  → Spawn at default position (cell 1.5, 1.5)

